17 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
18 SECTION 1. A. From the funds appropriated to the Office of
19 Educational Quality and Accountability in Enrolled House Bill No.
20 2766 of the 1st Session of the 60th Oklahoma Legislature, the sum of
21 Five Hundred Thousand Dollars ($500,000.00) shall be used to provide
22 grants to school districts in this state to provide a cellphone-free
23 educational environment. Grants shall be provided on a first-come,
24 first-served basis only to school districts whose governing boards
Req. No. 2156 Page 1

1 of e ducation have adopted a policy prohibiting students from using
2 cell phones and personal electronic devices while on the campus of a
3 public school district from bell to bell for three (3) school years,
4 beginning with the 2025-2026 school year.
5 B. Grants awarded pursuant to this section shall be used during
6 the 2025-2026 school year to purchase devices or equipment in which
7 students enrolled in a grant recipient school district can store
8 their cell phones and personal electronic devices during the school
9 day. In conjunction with the Office of Management and Enterprise
10 Services, the Office of Educational Quality and Accountability may
11 negotiate and enter into a contract with a vendor to offer a state
12 rate price to grant recipient school districts; provided, however, a
13 grant recipient school district shall not be required to use a
14 vendor contracted by the Office of Educational Quality and
15 Accountability.
16 C. Grant recipient school districts shall electronically submit
17 a report to the Office of Educational Quality and Accountability
18 detailing how grant funds were used.
19 D. The Commission for Educational Quality and Accountability
20 shall be authorized to promulgate rules in order to effectuate the
21 provisions of this section.
22 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 3. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health, or safety, an emergency is hereby
